The Yola Electricity Distribution Company (YEDC), has organized stakeholder consultation on the extra ordinary review of multi-year traffic order (MYTO), for Adamawa, Taraba and Yobe states. Engr Mustpha Umara, while clearing open the meeting Thursday in Yola, urged customers to contributes idea towards repositioning the company ahead of the April new traffic. Umara disclosed that, the company is expected to provide 400,000 prepared meters to customers for year 2020-2021. He said the proposed traffic if approved, would provide the company the needed funds to increase its efficiency in the value chain and address impending challenges. The meeting which is in pursuant to the Nigerian Electricity Regulatory Commission (NERC)’s directives provided platform for customers and stakeholders under the company. The MD assured customers that the company would stick to its unbiased services to all manner of customers, adding that customer merger addressed. A customer Mrs Jummai Zelani, who is into hair dressing business hopes that, with the new traffic would improve supply to boost her business. He enjoined interest customers can also get a copy of the consultation paper from all YEDC customer care units in any of the Business Units nearest to you. Head marketing and customer care, Mustapha Usman assured, that the revenue from the new tariff would be committed to eliminating inefficiency of the company. 